{
  "doc_id": "10881",
  "text": "The derivation of L λ,Σ tac was achieved by several groups of people: Adler, Ferrari and van Moerbeke got a multi-time tacnode kernel formula with λ = 1 from a discrete random walk model [CITATION_1] ; Delvaux, Kuijlaars and Zhang got a single time tacnode kernel formula from the nonintersecting Brownian motion model [CITATION_2] ; Johansson got a multi-time tacnode kernel formula with λ = 1 from the nonintersecting Brownian motion model [CITATION_3] ; Ferrari and Vető generalized Johansson's result for general λ > 0 [CITATION_4] 1 . The formulas of Adler-Ferrari-van Moerbeke and Johansson were both expressed in terms of Airy resolvents, but quite different in structure. They were later was proved to be equivalent [CITATION_5] . Delvaux-Kuijlaars-Zhang's formula was expressed by the tacnode RHP (their paper first defined the tacnode RHP, and the RHP is named thereby). Later Delvaux showed in [CITATION_6] the equivalence of the results in [CITATION_7] and [CITATION_8] , and furthermore wrote the general multi-time tacnode kernel in the tacnode Riemann-Hilbert problem. See also [CITATION_9] . A variation of the model where the nonintersecting Brownian bridges are on a circle was studied by the current authors in [CITATION_10] .",
